042019.note: To think of it another way, if you start with stored energy ' glucose or fat, for example, which if burned in calorimeter will give off varying amounts of heat ' and you're willing to convert their carbon, hydrogen, and oxygen molecules into another form with less energy ' water and carbon dioxide which, if burned, produce very little heat ' it's a fair trade!
